#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:3
msgid "Proximal Policy Optimization"
msgstr "近端策略優化 (Proximal Policy Optimization)"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:6
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:9
msgid "Background"
msgstr "背景"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:12
msgid "(Previously: `Background for TRPO`_)"
msgstr "（先前章節：`Background for TRPO`_）"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:16
msgid ""
"PPO is motivated by the same question as TRPO: how can we take the "
"biggest possible improvement step on a policy using the data we currently"
" have, without stepping so far that we accidentally cause performance "
"collapse? Where TRPO tries to solve this problem with a complex second-"
"order method, PPO is a family of first-order methods that use a few other"
" tricks to keep new policies close to old. PPO methods are significantly "
"simpler to implement, and empirically seem to perform at least as well as"
" TRPO."
msgstr ""
"PPO 的動機與 TRPO 相同：如何利用目前擁有的資料，在策略上邁出盡可能大的改進步"
"伐，同時不會因步伐過大而意外導致性能崩潰？TRPO 試圖用複雜的二階方法來解決這"
"個問題，而 PPO 是一系列一階方法，使用一些其他技巧來保持新策略與舊策略的接近。"
"PPO 的方法在實作上簡單得多，且在經驗上表現至少與 TRPO 一樣好。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:18
msgid "There are two primary variants of PPO: PPO-Penalty and PPO-Clip."
msgstr "PPO 有兩個主要變體：PPO-Penalty 和 PPO-Clip。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:20
msgid ""
"**PPO-Penalty** approximately solves a KL-constrained update like TRPO, "
"but penalizes the KL-divergence in the objective function instead of "
"making it a hard constraint, and automatically adjusts the penalty "
"coefficient over the course of training so that it's scaled "
"appropriately."
msgstr ""
"**PPO-Penalty** 近似地解決了像 TRPO 一樣的 KL 約束更新問題，但將 KL 散度 "
"(KL-Divergence) 作為目標函數中的懲罰項，而非硬約束，並在訓練過程中自動調整懲"
"罰係數以使其適當縮放。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:22
msgid ""
"**PPO-Clip** doesn't have a KL-divergence term in the objective and "
"doesn't have a constraint at all. Instead relies on specialized clipping "
"in the objective function to remove incentives for the new policy to get "
"far from the old policy."
msgstr ""
"**PPO-Clip** 在目標函數中沒有 KL 散度項，也完全沒有約束條件。它依賴目標函數中"
"特殊的裁剪 (Clipping) 機制，來消除新策略偏離舊策略的動機。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:24
msgid "Here, we'll focus only on PPO-Clip (the primary variant used at OpenAI)."
msgstr "在此，我們僅專注於 PPO-Clip（OpenAI 使用的主要變體）。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:27
msgid "Quick Facts"
msgstr "快速概覽"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:29
msgid "PPO is an on-policy algorithm."
msgstr "PPO 是一種同策略 (On-policy) 演算法。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:30
msgid ""
"PPO can be used for environments with either discrete or continuous "
"action spaces."
msgstr "PPO 可用於具有離散或連續動作空間 (Action Space) 的環境。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:31
msgid "The Spinning Up implementation of PPO supports parallelization with MPI."
msgstr "Spinning Up 的 PPO 實作支援透過 MPI 進行平行化。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:34
msgid "Key Equations"
msgstr "關鍵方程式"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:36
msgid "PPO-clip updates policies via"
msgstr "PPO-Clip 透過以下方式更新策略"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:38
msgid ""
"\\theta_{k+1} = \\arg \\max_{\\theta} \\underset{s,a \\sim "
"\\pi_{\\theta_k}}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[\n"
"    L(s,a,\\theta_k, \\theta)\\right],"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:43
msgid ""
"typically taking multiple steps of (usually minibatch) SGD to maximize "
"the objective. Here :math:`L` is given by"
msgstr ""
"通常透過多步（通常是小批次）SGD 來最大化目標函數。這裡 :math:`L` 定義為"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:45
msgid ""
"L(s,a,\\theta_k,\\theta) = \\min\\left(\n"
"\\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)}  "
"A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a), \\;\\;\n"
"\\text{clip}\\left(\\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)}, 1 "
"- \\epsilon, 1+\\epsilon \\right) A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)\n"
"\\right),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:52
msgid ""
"in which :math:`\\epsilon` is a (small) hyperparameter which roughly says"
" how far away the new policy is allowed to go from the old."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`\\epsilon` 是一個（較小的）超參數，大致決定了新策略允許偏離舊策略"
"的程度。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:54
msgid ""
"This is a pretty complex expression, and it's hard to tell at first "
"glance what it's doing, or how it helps keep the new policy close to the "
"old policy. As it turns out, there's a considerably simplified version "
"[1]_ of this objective which is a bit easier to grapple with (and is also"
" the version we implement in our code):"
msgstr ""
"這是一個相當複雜的表達式，乍看之下很難理解它在做什麼，或者它如何幫助保持新策"
"略接近舊策略。事實上，存在一個大幅簡化的版本 [1]_，更容易理解（也是我們在程式"
"碼中實作的版本）："

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:56
msgid ""
"L(s,a,\\theta_k,\\theta) = \\min\\left(\n"
"\\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)}  "
"A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a), \\;\\;\n"
"g(\\epsilon, A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a))\n"
"\\right),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:63
msgid "where"
msgstr "其中"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:65
msgid ""
"g(\\epsilon, A) = \\left\\{\n"
"    \\begin{array}{ll}\n"
"    (1 + \\epsilon) A & A \\geq 0 \\\\\n"
"    (1 - \\epsilon) A & A < 0.\n"
"    \\end{array}\n"
"    \\right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:74
msgid ""
"To figure out what intuition to take away from this, let's look at a "
"single state-action pair :math:`(s,a)`, and think of cases."
msgstr ""
"為了弄清楚從中可以得到什麼直覺，讓我們看一個單一的狀態-動作對 "
":math:`(s,a)`，並考慮不同情況。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:76
msgid ""
"**Advantage is positive**: Suppose the advantage for that state-action "
"pair is positive, in which case its contribution to the objective reduces"
" to"
msgstr ""
"**優勢為正**：假設該狀態-動作對的優勢函數 (Advantage Function) 為正，這種情況"
"下它對目標函數的貢獻簡化為"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:78
msgid ""
"L(s,a,\\theta_k,\\theta) = \\min\\left(\n"
"\\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)}, (1 + \\epsilon)\n"
"\\right)  A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:84
msgid ""
"Because the advantage is positive, the objective will increase if the "
"action becomes more likely---that is, if :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)` "
"increases. But the min in this term puts a limit to how *much* the "
"objective can increase. Once :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s) > (1+\\epsilon) "
"\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)`, the min kicks in and this term hits a ceiling of "
":math:`(1+\\epsilon) A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)`. Thus: *the new policy "
"does not benefit by going far away from the old policy*."
msgstr ""
"因為優勢為正，如果動作變得更有可能——即 :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)` 增大——目標"
"函數就會增加。但這一項中的 min 對目標函數能增加*多少*設了上限。一旦 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s) > (1+\\epsilon) \\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)`，min 就會"
"生效，該項達到 :math:`(1+\\epsilon) A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)` 的上界。因此："
"*新策略不會因遠離舊策略而獲益*。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:86
msgid ""
"**Advantage is negative**: Suppose the advantage for that state-action "
"pair is negative, in which case its contribution to the objective reduces"
" to"
msgstr ""
"**優勢為負**：假設該狀態-動作對的優勢為負，這種情況下它對目標函數的貢獻簡化為"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:88
msgid ""
"L(s,a,\\theta_k,\\theta) = \\max\\left(\n"
"\\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)}, (1 - \\epsilon)\n"
"\\right)  A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:94
msgid ""
"Because the advantage is negative, the objective will increase if the "
"action becomes less likely---that is, if :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)` "
"decreases. But the max in this term puts a limit to how *much* the "
"objective can increase. Once :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s) < (1-\\epsilon) "
"\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)`, the max kicks in and this term hits a ceiling of "
":math:`(1-\\epsilon) A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)`. Thus, again: *the new "
"policy does not benefit by going far away from the old policy*."
msgstr ""
"因為優勢為負，如果動作變得更不可能——即 :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)` 減小——目標"
"函數就會增加。但這一項中的 max 對目標函數能增加*多少*設了上限。一旦 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s) < (1-\\epsilon) \\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)`，max 就會"
"生效，該項達到 :math:`(1-\\epsilon) A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)` 的上界。因此，"
"再次說明：*新策略不會因遠離舊策略而獲益*。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:96
msgid ""
"What we have seen so far is that clipping serves as a regularizer by "
"removing incentives for the policy to change dramatically, and the "
"hyperparameter :math:`\\epsilon` corresponds to how far away the new "
"policy can go from the old while still profiting the objective."
msgstr ""
"到目前為止我們所看到的是，裁剪作為一種正則化手段，消除了策略劇烈變化的動機，"
"而超參數 :math:`\\epsilon` 對應著新策略在仍能使目標函數獲益的情況下，可以偏離"
"舊策略的程度。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:98 ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:155
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:100
msgid ""
"While this kind of clipping goes a long way towards ensuring reasonable "
"policy updates, it is still possible to end up with a new policy which is"
" too far from the old policy, and there are a bunch of tricks used by "
"different PPO implementations to stave this off. In our implementation "
"here, we use a particularly simple method: early stopping. If the mean "
"KL-divergence of the new policy from the old grows beyond a threshold, we"
" stop taking gradient steps."
msgstr ""
"雖然這種裁剪機制在確保合理的策略更新方面走了很長一段路，但仍有可能得到一個與"
"舊策略相差過遠的新策略，不同的 PPO 實作使用了各種技巧來避免這種情況。在我們的"
"實作中，我們使用了一種特別簡單的方法：提前停止 (Early Stopping)。如果新策略與"
"舊策略的平均 KL 散度超過閾值，我們就停止進行梯度更新。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:102
msgid ""
"When you feel comfortable with the basic math and implementation details,"
" it's worth checking out other implementations to see how they handle "
"this issue!"
msgstr ""
"當你對基本數學和實作細節感到自在時，值得去查看其他實作是如何處理這個問題的！"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:105
msgid ""
"See `this note`_ for a derivation of the simplified form of the PPO-Clip "
"objective."
msgstr "參見 `this note`_ 以獲得 PPO-Clip 目標函數簡化形式的推導。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:112
msgid "Exploration vs. Exploitation"
msgstr "探索與利用"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:114
msgid ""
"PPO trains a stochastic policy in an on-policy way. This means that it "
"explores by sampling actions according to the latest version of its "
"stochastic policy. The amount of randomness in action selection depends "
"on both initial conditions and the training procedure. Over the course of"
" training, the policy typically becomes progressively less random, as the"
" update rule encourages it to exploit rewards that it has already found. "
"This may cause the policy to get trapped in local optima."
msgstr ""
"PPO 以同策略的方式訓練一個隨機策略 (Stochastic Policy)。這意味著它透過根據"
"最新版本的隨機策略取樣動作來進行探索 (Exploration)。動作選擇的隨機程度取決於"
"初始條件和訓練過程。在訓練過程中，策略通常會逐漸變得不那麼隨機，因為更新規則"
"會鼓勵它利用 (Exploitation) 已經發現的獎勵。這可能導致策略陷入局部最優解 "
"(Local Optima)。"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:118
msgid "Pseudocode"
msgstr "虛擬碼"

#: ../../algorithms/ppo.rst:120
msgid ""
"\\begin{algorithm}[H]\n"
"    \\caption{PPO-Clip}\n"
"    \\label{alg1}\n"
"\\begin{algorithmic}[1]\n"
"    \\STATE Input: initial policy parameters $\\theta_0$, initial value "
"function parameters $\\phi_0$\n"
"    \\FOR{$k = 0,1,2,...$}\n"
"    \\STATE Collect set of trajectories ${\\mathcal D}_k = \\{\\tau_i\\}$"
" by running policy $\\pi_k = \\pi(\\theta_k)$ in the environment.\n"
"    \\STATE Compute rewards-to-go $\\hat{R}_t$.\n"
"    \\STATE Compute advantage estimates, $\\hat{A}_t$ (using any method "
"of advantage estimation) based on the current value function "
"$V_{\\phi_k}$.\n"
"    \\STATE Update the policy by maximizing the PPO-Clip objective:\n"
"        \\begin{equation*}\n"
"        \\theta_{k+1} = \\arg \\max_{\\theta} \\frac{1}{|{\\mathcal D}_k|"
" T} \\sum_{\\tau \\in {\\mathcal D}_k} \\sum_{t=0}^T \\min\\left(\n"
"            \\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a_t|s_t)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a_t|s_t)}  "
"A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s_t,a_t), \\;\\;\n"
"            g(\\epsilon, A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s_t,a_t))\n"
"        \\right),\n"
"        \\end{equation*}\n"
"        typically via stochastic gradient ascent with Adam.\n"
"    \\STATE Fit value function by regression on mean-squared error:\n"
"        \\begin{equation*}\n"
"        \\phi_{k+1} = \\arg \\min_{\\phi} \\frac{1}{|{\\mathcal D}_k| T} "
"\\sum_{\\tau \\in {\\mathcal D}_k} \\sum_{t=0}^T\\left( V_{\\phi} (s_t) -"
" \\hat{R}_t \\right)^2,\n"
"        \\end{equation*}\n"
"        typically via some gradient descent algorithm.\n"
"    \\ENDFOR\n"
"\\end{algorithmic}\n"
"\\end{algorithm}"
msgstr ""

